                <h1>"Effective Use of Placeholder Images in Design"</h1>
                <p>A placeholder image serves as a temporary visual element in design and web development, ensuring that users understand where an image will be placed. These images can improve user experience by maintaining layout consistency while the actual images are being created or sourced. They are essential for prototyping and layout design.</p>
